quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  21,51,"Even before that We blessed Abraham with rectitude, for We knew him well"
  21,52,"Remember that occasion when Abraham asked his father and his people, \"What are these images to which you are so devoted"
  21,53,"They replied, \"We found our forefathers worshipping them"
  21,54,"He said \"Then certainly both you and your forefathers have been in manifest error"
  21,55,"They asked, \"Have you brought us the Truth or are you one of the triflers"
  21,56,"He replied, \"Nay! Your Lord is the Lord of the heavens and the earth. It is He Who has created them; and I am of those who bear witness to this"
  21,57,By Allah! I will certainly plan against your idols when you turn and go away
  21,58,"So he broke them all in pieces, except the biggest of them, so that they might turn to it"
  21,59,"(On their return when they saw the plight of their idols), some asked, \"Who has done this to our gods? He must surely be a wicked person"
  21,60,"Others replied, \"We heard a youth, called Abraham, talking about them"
  21,61,"They said, \"Then bring him here before the eyes of the people, so that they may witness how severely he is punished"
  21,62,"When Abraham came, they asked, \"O Abraham, are you the one who has done this to our gods"
  21,63,"He replied, \"Surely someone has done it; the chief of them, that is! Ask them, if they can speak"
  21,64,"Thereupon they turned to search their own consciences, and said to themselves, \"Surely you yourselves are the wrongdoers"
  21,65,"Confounded as they were, lowering their heads they said, \"You know fully well that they cannot speak"
  21,66,"At this Abraham said, \"Do you then worship these deities, instead of Allah, who can neither benefit nor harm you"
  21,67,Shame on you and on those deities you worship besides Allah! Have you no sense at all
  21,68,"They cried, \"Burn him alive and avenge your gods, if you want to take any action"
  21,69,"When they threw him in the fire, We commanded, \"O fire! Be cool and comfortable for Abraham"
  21,70,"They sought to harm him, but We made them the big losers"
  21,71,We delivered him and his nephew Lot and directed them to the land which We have blessed for all the people of the world
  21,72,We gave him a son Isaac and then a grandson Jacob; and We made each of them a righteous man
  21,73,"We made them leaders who guided other people by Our command and We sent them revelations to do good deeds, establish Salah and pay Zakah. To Us Alone did they serve"
  21,74,"To Lot We gave wisdom and knowledge, and We delivered him from the town which practiced abominations - surely its inhabitants were very wicked transgressors"
  21,75,"and We admitted him to Our mercy: for he was of the righteous people"
  21,76,"Before them Noah prayed to Us, We accepted his prayer and delivered him and his family from the great calamity"
  21,77,"We helped him against those people who had denied Our revelations; surely they were an evil people, so We drowned them all in the Great Flood"
  21,78,"We also bestowed favors upon Davidand Solomon: when the two were judging a case regarding the field into which the sheep of certain people had strayed by night, and We were watching them to arrive at judgment"
  21,79,"at that time We gave Solomon insight to arrive at the right decision, although We had given wisdom and knowledge to both of them. We caused the mountains and the birds to celebrate Our praises with David; it was We Who made this happen"
  21,80,"We taught him the armor’s craft, so that they might protect you in your wars: yet are you ever grateful"
  21,81,"We made the raging winds subservient to Solomon, pursuing its course by his command to the land which We had blessed; and We have knowledge of everything"
  21,82,And We had subjected to him many of the Satans who dived for him into the sea and performed other duties besides this; and We were the One Who had control over them for him